        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:5:2:9:2",
        "text": [
          " سَمِعْتُ أَبَا الْحَسَنِ مُوسَى ( عليه السلام ) يَقُولُ إِنَّ اللَّهَ جَلَّ وَ عَزَّ يُبْغِضُ الْعَبْدَ النَّوَّامَ الْفَارِغَ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ibn Fazzal, from the one who mentioned it, from Bashir Al Dahhan who said, ",
            "‘I heard Abu Al-Hassan Musa<sup>asws</sup> saying: ‘Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Majestic and Mighty Hates the sleeping and the leisurely servant’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "2. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from ibn Faddal from the one whom he has mentioned (in his book) from Bashir al-Dahhan who has said the following: “I heard abu al-Hassan, Musa, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, saying, ’Allah, most Majestic, most Glorious, dislikes an excessively sleeping servant who passes his time without work.’” "
          ]
        }
